com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core
Interface Unit

All Superinterfaces:
DeployModelObject
All Known Subinterfaces:
ConceptualNode, SoftwareComponent
public interface Unit
extends DeployModelObject

A representation of the model object 'Unit'. Represents an abstract unit of publishable deployment.

A unit is an contains provided Capability instances, and consumed Requirement instances. In is contained in a Topology. A unit can be published to the modeled infrastructure using a deployment publisher. It has hosting and dependency requirements.

Typically, unit subtypes are defined as tag types and do not add attributes. The tag is used by publishers to identify the driver responsible for provisioning the unit in the infrastructure. Unit properties are typically associated with subtypes of Capability. In the first release of the Topology Definition Model (TDM) the schema does not enforce the association between unit and capability types. Modelers create templates which are instances of unit subtypes containing predefined sets of capabilities and requirements.

The following features are supported:

  • Build Version
  • Conceptual
  • Configuration Unit
  • Goal Install State
  • Init Install State
  • Origin
  • Publish Intent

CorePackage.getUnit()

getConstraintLinks

java.util.List getConstraintLinks()
Returns the list of Constraint Links contained in the Unit. Constraint Links contained in a Unit should be links that have as their source a DeployModelObject that is contained (directly, or indirectly) in the unit. The code that creates a new Constraint Link should make sure that the link is added to the list of Constraint Links of the appropriate unit.

isHosting

boolean isHosting(Unit hostedUnit,
                  boolean checkContained)
Used to test if the passed hostedUnit is being hosted by this Unit. This method will look for HostingLinks with wth hosted type being equal to the passed hostedUnit.

The checkedContained will be used to test contained Units as well.

Parameters:
hostedUnit - - The Unit to test for hosted.
checkContained - - A boolean used to test the contained Units as ell.
Returns:
A boolean indicating if the hostedUnit is being hosted by this Unit.

getSpecializedTypeId

java.lang.String getSpecializedTypeId()
Get the specialized type id for this unit type. Take into account any specialization logic that determines the type. As for example, a WebsphereAppServer unit can have specialized type id for version v6 and version 6.1. If you need to define UnitFilters for a unit specialization, then you must override this method.

Returns:
String the specialized type id
